B&H Warranty/Imported/Grey Market Products
What is a B&H Warranty item?
Items labeled with a B&H Warranty are imported or grey market products that are being sold outside of the manufacturer's intended sales region. Products obtained from sources other than the manufacturer or its licensed importer are "grey market" products. Grey market is not illegal, not factory seconds, not demo merchandise, not cheaper or inferior quality. In fact, in almost every instance, a grey market product is absolutely identical to its USA-warranted counterpart. Grey market and USA-warranted products are manufactured in the same factories, from the same components and sub-assemblies, to the same specs and tolerances, and by the same workers. In terms of the items themselves, there is no difference at all. For example: a grey market Nikon 50mm f/1.4 D-AF lens is exactly the same in every possible way as a USA-warranted version. You may see such items also described as "Imported" or "Grey Market" or "International."
Why does B&H sell Imported items?
Product availability — by selling Imported items, we're able to offer items that may currently be unavailable directly from manufacturers.
What are the key differences between Imported and Regular items?
Imported items are not warranted by the manufacturer and, instead, come with a limited warranty from B&H. Additionally, these items are not eligible for Rebates or promotional offers from the manufacturer.
Are grey market items eligible for manufacturer repair if damaged and out of warranty period?
While each manufacturer is different, many manufacturers do not provide an option for repair on items that are labelled as grey market merchandise.
Are there any other differences?
Typically, there are no other major differences in how the items function. There may be some slight changes to how the menu system is organized, which languages are set as default, or the literature included with the item. Functionally, the items are the same.
What are B&H's warranty terms?
We cover all manufacturing defects. Duration varies based on the item. Please see the product page and locate the "In the Box" section for duration of coverage. Typically this will match the manufacturer's standard warranty.
Who do I contact for warranty service?
Contact B&H customer service for any service questions.
Can I purchase an extended warranty on grey market items that come with a B&H warranty?
Yes. Customers can purchase an extended warranty in the exact same way as they would with an item with a standard manufacturer's warranty.
Privacy & Security
B&H Foto & Electronics Corp - Web Privacy Policy. Version Effective September 26, 2023
A. Who we are
B & H Foto & Electronics Corp ("B&H") is the largest non-chain photo, video and consumer electronics store in the United States. The business operates a retail store on 34th St. and 9th Avenue in New York City, along with their main website (
www.bhphotovideo.com
), mobile application and content delivery site, "B&H Explora" (
www.bhphotovideo.com/explora
).
Due to the nature of the retail and eCommerce business, B&H is often required to obtain Personal Information from our consumers, organizational sales customers, affiliates and vendors to successfully operate. B&H recognizes the need to maintain the confidentiality of private, highly confidential and proprietary information. This Data Privacy Policy ("Policy") will offer a transparent breakdown of how B&H and our strategic partners protect the confidentiality of the information collected by B&H.
B&H is a "Data Controller", a legal term which means we make decisions regarding how and why we collect and use your Personal Information. As the "Data Controller", we are responsible for ensuring that your Personal Information is only used for the purposes for which it was originally collected and in compliance with all applicable data protection laws. We are also responsible for ensuring that any third party that we authorize to process the data on our behalf, known as "Data Processors", also follow these standards and use the data only for these same reasons.
If you have concerns or questions regarding this privacy policy, the use and collection of your Personal Information by B&H, or if you require more details on how we collect, store or use your Personal Information, you can email
privacy@bhphoto.com
.
You may also write to us at the following address:
Privacy Team, Legal Department
B & H Foto & Electronics Corp.
420 Ninth Avenue
New York, NY 10001
800-606-6969 or 212-444-6615
This Policy should be read in conjunction with all the
B&H Website Terms and Conditions.
B. Changes to B&H Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify this privacy policy. When we make changes, the updated policy will be posted here and the revision date will be updated. You are encouraged to refer back to ensure you are familiar with our most recent policy updates.
C. Purpose of this policy
This Policy covers B&H and its affiliated Partners. It explains the Legal Basis that B&H has in processing your Personal Information, how and what data we collect about you and what we do with that data. This policy will also inform you of your data privacy rights and how you can exercise those rights.
In this policy, when we talk about "Personal Information", we are referring to any information that relates to you, such as your name, email address, mailing address, telephone number, etc.
When we talk about the B&H Platform we mean the B&H
websites,
www.bhphotovideo.com
and
www.bhphotovideo.com/explora
, 
and the B&H mobile application.
For specific information about  the EU-US Data Privacy Framework Program, See Section L below.
D. The data we collect from you and how we collect that data
We collect Personal Information directly from you and from any devices, including mobile devices, that you use when you use our Platform, register for an account with us, provide us with information on a web form, update or add information to your account, participate in a community board discussion chat, or when you otherwise correspond with us.
The provision of Personal Information is voluntary but may be necessary in order to use our Services, such as setting up an account, conducting a transaction, commenting on a blog post or reviewing a product.
1. Personal Information you give us when you use our Services or register for an account with us
Account Registration:
Identifying information such as your name, addresses, telephone numbers or email addresses when you register for an account with us.
Purchases:
Name, telephone number, email address, mailing address, billing and other information used to process an order and send you the items you purchased. If needed, information required to clear customs (such as Tax ID or other identification numbers) and relevant postage information (such as tracking numbers and tracking updates) may be collected as well.
Communicating with Us:
You may also provide us with additional information through a web form, by updating or adding information to your account, through your participation in blog posts, community discussions, and chats, or when you otherwise communicate with us regarding our Services.
Events:
You may provide us with your name and contact information when you register for an event on our website or in our store.
Authentication:
Additional information we are required or authorized by applicable national laws to collect and process in order to authenticate or identify you or to verify the information we have collected.
Used Item Sales:
When selling a used item to B&H, it is required that B&H collect a copy of a valid government issued ID.
B&H does not collect credit card or other financial information from you; that information is collected directly by our trusted third party payment processing partners. On occasion, for some international customers B&H will require bank account information.
If you give us Personal Information about someone else, including pictures of them, their name, their e-mail address, etc., on our social media Platforms, e-views and comments on our websites, you must do so only if you have that person's consent to provide us with that information. You should direct them to this policy so that they are informed about how we collect, use, disclose, and retain their Personal Information. Please see our website
user agreement
for how we may use and retain any content submitted to us.
2. Personal Information we collect automatically when you use our Services or register for an account with us
Advertising:
We collect information about your interaction with our Services, your advertising preferences and your communications with us. This is information we receive from devices (including mobile devices) you use when you access our Services. This information could include the following: Device ID or unique identifier, device type, ID for advertising and a unique device token.
Advertising Analytics:
Computer and connection information such as statistics on your page views, traffic to and from the sites, referral URL, ad data, your IP address, your browsing activity, history and your web log information.
3. Personal Information we collect using cookies and similar technologies
We use cookies, web beacons, unique identifiers and similar technologies to collect information about the pages you view, the links you click on and other actions you take when using our Services, within our advertising or email content.
For more information about our use of these technologies, and how to control them, see section on Cookies (Section I).
4. Personal Information we collect from third parties
Marketing:
On occasion we might collect Personal Information from third parties such as tradeshows or email lists to market our products and services to you. This information is usually limited to name, email address and, rarely, mailing addresses.
5. Linking to External Websites
B&H sites such as Explora can contain links to external sites and social media pages, including those of photographers, artists, and other contributors. B&H does not assume responsibility and is not liable for your data privacy on any external sites. Please consult the privacy policy of the site/s.
E. EEA Your personal data rights
Under the GDPR, residents and nationals of the EEA have the following data rights:
Right to be informed:
You have a right to know what Personal Information we collect from you, how we collect it and what we use it for. You will find that information in this policy.
Right to request access:
You have the right to request access to the Personal Information held about you, to obtain confirmation that it is being processed, and to obtain certain prescribed information about how we process it.
Right to object:
applies to the processing of your Personal Information where it is based on Legitimate Interests and where your data is processed for direct marketing or processed for the purposes of collating statistical information.
Right to restrict processing:
or 'block' the use of your Personal Information, for instance where you believe your Personal Information is not accurate (until the accuracy can be verified).
Right to Erasure:
The right to have your Personal Information erased, also known as the "right to be forgotten" 
	enables you to request the deletion or removal of Personal Information where there is no compelling reason for its continued use. Requests for erasure may be
	refused in some circumstances, such as where the Personal Information must be retained to comply with a legal obligation or to exercise or defend legal claims.
Right to rectification:
You have the right to request to have your Personal Information corrected if it is inaccurate and to have incomplete Personal Information completed in certain circumstances.
The right to data portability
allows you to obtain and reuse your Personal Information for your own purposes across
	different services; to move copy or transfer your Personal Information easily from one environment to another in a safe and secure way without hindrance to usability.
You may exercise your rights in relation to
automated decision making
in circumstances which have a legal effect or otherwise significantly affects you. This right allows individuals in certain circumstances to access certain safeguards 
    against the risk that a potentially damaging decision is taken solely without human intervention. In specific instances, you have the right to request human
	intervention and an explanation of the automated decision, and you may be able to challenge that decision.
If you are a resident or national of the European Economic Area (EEA) and would like to exercise your individual data subject access rights, 
please call toll free
800.947.9915
or email
privacy@bhphoto.com
.
To make a data-privacy related request, please call toll free
800.947.9915
or email
privacy@bhphoto.com
. You can also reach our Data Protection Officer at
dpo@bhphoto.com
for any other inquiries related to our handling of your personal information.
F. California Privacy Notice
California Personal Information Rights:
Under the California Consumer Protection Act, California residents have the following data rights:
Right to know about personal information collected, disclosed, or sold:
You have the right to request a list of the categories of your
   	personal information we have collected and used within the last 12 months. You are also entitled to receive a) information identifying all third-party
    companies to whom B&H may have disclosed, within the last 12 months, personal information pertaining to you and your family; and b) a description of the
    categories of personal information disclosed. You can also find a list of the categories of information we collect and disclose about you elsewhere in our
    privacy policy. To request a list of the information we collect about you, email
privacy@bhphoto.com
. 
    Once the request has been received, you may be asked to provide additional personal information for verification purposes, including your name, email address, telephone number, physical address and previous order history before your request can be accommodated. For requests involving specific pieces of information, 
    we may also require you to sign a declaration under penalty of perjury that you are the consumer whose personal information is the subject of the request.
Right to request deletion of personal information
: You have the right to request that we
  	delete any personal information we have collected about you provided we do not need to retain the information 
  	for legitimate business or legal reasons. To request that your information be deleted from our system, please email
privacy@bhphoto.com
with your request. Once the 
  	request has been received, you may be asked to provide additional identifying information for 
  	verification purposes, including your name, email address, telephone number, physical address and previous order history before your request can be accommodated.
Right to opt-out of the sale of personal information:
As a California resident, you have the right to opt-out of the sale of your personal information by a business to a third party. 
  B&H does not sell customer information to third parties.
Right to non-discrimination for the exercise of your privacy rights
: B&H respects and values the privacy rights of our consumers, and we do not 
  	discriminate against customers who exercise their privacy rights under California law or any other law.
Authorized Agent:
As a California consumer, you have the right to have someone else make requests for you under the CCPA. For requests made by an authorized agent, we may require you to provide written proof of authorization and to verify your own identity directly with us (as described above).
For more general information on our privacy policies and business practices, please see the rest of our privacy policy or email
legal@bhphoto.com
.
How to Make a Request:
To make a data privacy related request, please call toll free
800.947.9915
or email
privacy@bhphoto.com
. Once the request has been received, you may be asked to provide additional personal information for verification purposes before your request can be accommodated, including a combination of two or more of the following: email address, telephone number, billing address, previous purchase history and order information.  If you would like an authorized agent to make a request on your behalf, in addition to the information above, we will need written authorization from you identifying the authorized agent by name and email address and directing us to respond to the request the authorized agent is making on your behalf.
The "Legal Categories" of Personal Information We Collect About You:
California law requires us to tell you about the Personal Information we collect about you in a certain way - specifically, we need to tie it back to the "legal categories" of Personal Information that are listed in the law.  To do this, we bundled up the information we gave you in Section D of this policy and matched the different types of Personal Information we collect about you with the legal category.  To make things easier to understand, we've put this information in a
California Privacy Chart
at the end of this California Privacy Notice section.
Sharing Your Personal Information
This section will tell you about how we share your Personal Information with others.  First, we will tell you how we use and share your Personal Information for marketing purposes.  Then, you'll learn about how we share your information for business purposes.  We use the
California Privacy Chart
at the end of this California Privacy Notice section to match the "legal categories" of Personal Information with what we share, why we share it, and who we share it with.
Marketing.
Once you've made a purchase with us or registered for an account with us, we may use your name, email address, mailing address, and purchase history to contact you with information, special offers, or new products that we think you might be interested in.  We might also collect this Personal Information from third parties such as tradeshows or email lists to market our products and services to you. This information is usually limited to name, email address and, rarely, mailing addresses.  We may share this Personal Information with our Partners to provide you with special offers related to B&H.
Sharing for Business Purposes.
Except for marketing, we only share your information for our business purposes.  In other words, we only share your information to operate our business and for the purposes we've described in this privacy policy.  The list below tells you when we share your Personal Information for a business purpose and who we share it with.
Service Providers
: Other companies sometimes provide services to us or on our behalf.  For example, we may use other companies for IT support, order fulfillment, warranties, shipping and tracking, technology solutions, maintaining our website, fraud prevention, verification, and government policy compliance.
Third Parties with Whom You Ask Us to Share Your Personal Information
: If you ask us to share your Personal Information with a third party, we will only share the information that is needed to complete your request.  This can apply to any request you make, like warranty claims, store credit cards, manufacturers or suppliers, and other requests you might make.
Compliance with Legal Obligations
: We may need to disclose certain information to auditors, government authorities, law enforcement, regulatory agencies, our legal counsel, third-party litigants and their counsel, or other authorized individuals to comply with laws that apply to us, subpoenas, discovery requests, or other legal obligations such as contractual requirements.  This can include things like customs and used item sales.
Changes in Business Structure or Ownership
: We may disclose or transfer your Personal Information to a third party in the event of any reorganization, merger, sale, acquisition, joint venture, assignment, transfer, or other disposition of all or any portion of B&H's business, assets, or ownership interest (including through bankruptcy or similar proceedings).
B&H does not sell consumers' Personal Information to anyone.  The law also requires us to explicitly tell you that we do not sell the Personal Information of minors under 16 years old.
