I. B&H cookies
When you visit our Platform, we or our authorized service providers may use cookies, web beacons, and other similar technologies for storing information to help provide you with a better, faster, and safer experience for advertising purposes.
1. What is a Cookie
A Cookie is a small text file that a website stores on your PC, telephone or any other device, with information
	  	about your navigation on that website. Cookies are necessary to facilitate browsing and to make it more user-friendly. They do not damage your
	  	computer and are never used to store your sensitive Personal Information.
The purpose of using cookies is to improve your web browsing experience, enhance site security, and for marketing
		and promotional purposes. Cookies allow us to remember your preferences (like preferred language and country), estimate patterns of use, and provide improved
		search results. We also collect certain technical information from your computer, like your IP address and the address of a referring web site, if any.
		This information will allow us to enhance our site to match your preferences. This information is used only for the benefit of B&H, our authorized
		Partners and you, our customer.
You can visit our site without cookies if you choose to do so. However, please be aware that some features of
		the site may not function properly or may be slower if you refuse cookies. To visit our site without cookies, you can configure your web browser settings.
		Please check the browser's help menu to learn how to change your cookie preferences.
2. Types of Cookies on our Platform
There are several types of cookies that we may use on our site. These are constantly changing while we monitor and upgrade our site.
First Party Cookies:
These Cookies are set exclusively by us. We use both session and persistent Cookies.
Third Party Cookies:
These Cookies are set by our service providers at our request while on our Platform. They may be Session or Persistent cookies. These are cookies that sit out on 
	 			our Platform and are managed by third parties at our request, to provide services and improve the customer browsing experience. They may also be
			used to detect and prevent fraudulent activity. These cookies collect data about your activities while on our Platform and may be used to enhance the
			setting party's datasets. They can be used to serve advertising to you on our Platform and other websites.
We do not permit any third-party content on our Platform with the exception of our authorized
			service providers. If you have a concern about our, or our authorized third-party service providers Personal Information collection, please
contact us
.
3. Purposes for our Cookies:
We use cookies for the following purposes:
Essential Website Operations:
these technologies are strictly necessary to provide you with services available on our Platform and to use its features, such as adding products to a cart, 
					form submissions, video playback, etc. Turning these off would result in limited functionality being available on our Platform.
Performance and Functionality:
these technologies are used to enhance the functionality of our Platform but are not critical to their use. We recommend you use them, since that would give 
					you the best experience of our Platform.
Analytics:
these Cookies collect information that is used in aggregate form to help us understand how our
					websites are being used and to help us improve our Platform and provide you with a better experience.
Advertising:
these are technologies which help us make advertising messages more relevant to you. They collect behavioral information about your activities on our Platform 
					and perform functions like preventing the same ad from continuously appearing, ensuring ads are properly displayed and, in some cases, relevant to your interests. 
					These cookies may be used to serve ads for our products or products of third parties on our, or third party websites.
4. Managing your Cookie consent and preferences
At this time only customers accessing our Platform from EEA regions can update their cookie preferences
You have the ability to opt out of the use of our Cookies. Please visit our
Cookie
			Preferences Page
where you can manage your preferences for the types of Cookies listed above.
Should you wish to turn off all Cookies, you may do so in your browser's settings.
